The paper deals with algorithms for optimizing the diameter of a graph, specifically trees, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of an oracle to query weights suggests a focus on information theory (cs.IT) and the optimization of a metric property of the graph suggests a connection to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and possibly social and information networks (cs.SI).
